  <p>
    In this renovation project, I designed and implemented a Loxone smart home system. The system architecture was developed in collaboration with a licensed electrician and a certified Loxone installer. Following the design phase, I executed the physical wiring, programming, system commissioning, and troubleshooting.<br><br>The infrastructure is structured in three distribution boards: a main unit serving the ground floor and two sub-distribution boards for the upper and lower levels. The project also features complex automation for a dedicated wellness room.<br><br>Programmed via Loxone Config, the system integrates:<br>
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Lighting and shading (blinds)</li><li>Underfloor heating and boiler temperature control</li><li>Presence detection and intrusion alarms&nbsp;<br></li><li>Access control (Door locks, Intercom/Doorbell)</li><li>Wellness system controls (pool and sauna)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The home utilizes several logic modes to automate daily routines, to integrate into a persons life seamlessly:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Away Mode: Activates the alarm, closes blinds, turns off lights/motion detection, and lowers the temperature.</li><li>Sleep Mode: Modifies motion detection in bedrooms, dims lights, lowers temperature, closes blinds, and disables audio.</li><li>Lighting Scenes: Adapts internal brightness based on the sun's position and outdoor light intensity.</li><li>Overheating Protection: Automatically adjusts shading to block solar gain and prevent the rooms from overheating.</li>
  </ul>

